# AI service agent (AI lane)

## Scope

- **Only** edit files under `ai-service/`.
- Do not change `frontend/` or `backend/` unless user asks.

## Responsibility

- Stateless **ML inference & training** (XGBoost / scikit-learn per `docs/05-ai-forecasting.md`)
- **No** business auth, **no** PostgreSQL writes, **no** Gemini — those belong to **backend**

## Target layout

```
ai-service/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py
│   ├── routers/       # health, train, forecast
│   ├── schemas/       # Pydantic request/response
│   ├── services/      # preprocess, train, predict
│   └── saved_models/  # .joblib artifacts
├── requirements.txt
└── Dockerfile         # uvicorn app.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

## Endpoints (internal, port 8000)

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| GET | `/ai/health` | Liveness (Docker healthcheck) |
| POST | `/ai/train` | Train from sales-history JSON payload |
| POST | `/ai/forecast/all` | 30-day forecast for all products |
| GET | `/ai/model/metrics` | MAE, RMSE, MAPE |

## Contracts

- JSON in/out only; caller is Spring Boot WebClient
- Spec: `docs/04-api-specification.md`, `docs/05-ai-forecasting.md`
- Keep handlers fast; heavy work async only if already patterned in repo

## Out of scope for AI agent

- JWT, RBAC, `sales_orders` CRUD, React UI, Gemini chat
